expressivity.physicalContactObject: black and silver telescoping selfie stick with phone holder
expressivity.physicalSubstrateObject: black stainless steel Tesla-branded water bottle
expressivity.contactUtilizationMethod: Collapse one or two segments so the foam grip becomes the handle and keep the phone clamp closed to form a compact, heavier tip. The stick’s length, cylindrical grip, and noticeable weight at the clamp end give an excellent head-heavy hammer sensation when swung.
expressivity.substrateUtilizationMethod: Stand the bottle upright on the table. Strike the upper shoulder of the bottle with a downward swing. The first milliseconds deliver a hard, metallic stop, then the cylindrical shape instantly tips and rolls away, removing resistance. The quick transition from rigid impact to free follow-through mimics the moment the hammer bursts through the rind.
expressivity.expectedHapticFeedback: The user should then experience a distinct "breakthrough" moment as the hammer penetrates the rind - a sudden release of resistance like breaking through a moderately tough shell
expressivity.explanation: The steel bottle provides a sharp initial jolt and the tipping motion gives a clear release, but the metallic feel and low deformation limit the buildup and organic crack sensation.

realism.physicalSubstrateObject: black stainless steel Tesla-branded water bottle
realism.contactUtilizationMethod: Collapse one or two segments so the foam grip becomes the handle and keep the phone clamp closed to form a compact, heavier tip. The stick’s length, cylindrical grip, and noticeable weight at the clamp end give an excellent head-heavy hammer sensation when swung.
realism.substrateUtilizationMethod: Stand the bottle upright on the table. Strike the upper shoulder of the bottle with a downward swing. The first milliseconds deliver a hard, metallic stop, then the cylindrical shape instantly tips and rolls away, removing resistance. The quick transition from rigid impact to free follow-through mimics the moment the hammer bursts through the rind.
realism.expectedHapticFeedback: The user should then experience a distinct "breakthrough" moment as the hammer penetrates the rind - a sudden release of resistance like breaking through a moderately tough shell
realism.explanation: The steel shoulder gives a sharp impact and the bottle tipping provides a quick release, but the tension buildup is brief and the rolling motion only partially evokes a full log split.

Swinging it downward and compressing the soft paper on contact reproduces the motion pattern of a mallet while offering safe, cushioned stops.
realism.substrateUtilizationMethod: Partially extend the selfie-stick and stand it vertically with the phone clamp resting on the table and the handle pointing upward (so the thin telescopic tubes bear the load). Strike the centre of the top handle. The nested tubes resist through static friction, then suddenly slide downward once the threshold is exceeded, producing a quick drop in resistance that mimics the rind break.
realism.expectedHapticFeedback: The user should then experience a distinct "breakthrough" moment as the hammer penetrates the rind - a sudden release of resistance like breaking through a moderately tough shell
realism.explanation: The clang and sudden drop imitate the split-and-fall nicely, though the hollow metal resonance still feels less like dense wood.
